column6: First, she dreamed of little Alice herself, and once again the tiny hands were clasped upon her knee, and the bright eager eyes were looking up into hers - she could hear the very tones of her voice, and see that queer little toss of her head to keep back the wandering hair that would always get into her eyes - and still as she listened, or seemed to listen, the whole place around her became alive with the strange creatures of her little sister ’ s dream.
column7: Nejprve se jí zdálo o Alence, jak jí zase ručkama obmyká koleno a dychtivě na ni upírá bystrá očka - slyšela znovu zvuk jejího hlasu a viděla ji před sebou, jak tak zvláštně pohazuje hlavou a střásá dozadu tu neposlušnou kadeř, která jí pořád a pořád padá do očí - a jak ji tak poslouchala nebo se domnívala, že ji poslouchá, kolem dokola se to zahemžilo podivnými tvory ze snu její sestřičky.
